snippet: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel called King Abdullah II of Jordan, who withdrew his ambassador, to reassure him that Israel would maintain the status quo at the contested site.
abstract: Israel's Prime Min Benjamin Netanyahu seeks to reassure Jordan's King Abdullah II that Israel is committed to maintaining the status quo at a contested holy site in East Jerusalem, and that Israel will make every effort to restore calm.

byline.contributor: Rana F. Sweis contributed reporting from Amman, Jordan.

lead_paragraph: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu of Israel called King Abdullah II of Jordan, who withdrew his ambassador, to reassure him that Israel would maintain the status quo at the contested site.

headline.main: Israel Pledges to Restore Security at Religious Site
headline.print_headline: Israel Pledges to Restore Security at Religious Site
